<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-9955] Exceptions thrown from SinkTask::close shadow other exceptions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-9955</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If an exception is thrown from SinkTask::close, the exception will shadow any other previous exception, because SinkTask::close is called from within a finally block.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Steps to reproduce:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Throw an exception from SinkTask::start or SinkTask::put&#160;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Throw an exception from SinkTask::close&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Expected behavior:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;All exceptions are visible in separate log messages&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The error from SinkTask::start or SinkTask::put is logged as the exception that caused the task to stop.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Actual behavior:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The exception from SinkTask::close is logged as the exception that caused the task to stop.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The exceptions from either SinkTask::start or SinkTask::put are swallowed and don&apos;t appear in the logs at all.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
